@andrewjshults Glad you're interested in the Avro support! However, it has only recently been merged, so it isn't in a release yet. It landed after the 0.9.2 release, so it's expected that you wouldn't be able to install it via PyPI yet.

We'll have to wait until the next release to make it available from PyPI, but the alternative for the moment would be to use a reference to a specific git commit [as described in the pip VCS docs](https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/reference/pip_install/#vcs-support).

We can also potentially think about an intermediate release just so these features (and other bug fixes) become available sooner. I think the primary overhead would be running the release through the Kafka system test gauntlet that validates lots of functionality. At the moment that's a manual process (something @edenhill is anxious to automate).

